Voice of the Customer.

   Customers, whether satisfied or not, will rarely make their sentiments
   known. This is the great paradox of customer relations. Customers have
   never had as many tools to express themselves with as they do today,
   and yet, they often remain silent.

   “96% of dissatisfied customers do not express their sentiments directly
   to the company.”

   Here at Critizr we believe that a it is of upmost importance that
   customers be able to express themselves and be heard by companies.
   Our mission : offer a solution that allows companies to collect,
   process, measure and highlight their customers' feedback on one
   platform.

   Our solution is a reflection of our convictions, every customer should
   be able to express their thoughts about a product or a service whenever
   they wish to and with ease. To this end, we have created the
   Critizr.com website, which has enabled us to acquire a unique
   expertise in collecting and processing customer feedback throughout
   Europe.
   tiers-confiance-illustration.jpg
   tiers-confiance-floating.jpg
   Conviction 1_V3b

Listen

   Listening to your customers is a continuous, multi-channel process.
   Conviction 2_V3b

Trust

   To provide their feedback, customers need to feel reassured by and have
   trust in you.
   Conviction 3_V2-1b

Company wide

   The feedback data collected should be of use to the entire company.
   Conviction 4_V3b

Engagement

   Customer satisfaction isn't enough. You need to aim for customer
   engagement.
   Découvrez nos 10 convictions

All-In-One Platform

   Critizr offers a complete platform streamlining data collection,
   processing, and measurement-harvesting the full value from your
   customers' feedback.
     * Collect
     * Processing
     * Measurement
     * Value

The most complete solution on the market

   Today, customers should be able to express themselves whenever they may
   feel inclined, at any point during their customer experience. By
   combining spontaneous and solicited feedback, you will increase the
   value of your sample size by capturing the full range of your
   customers' experience.

   Collect evaluations (NPS, CSAT, testimonials, etc.) to better
   understand your customers thanks to the two approaches of push
   (solicited) and pull (spontaneous).
   COLLECTE V4

Centralized access to customer knowledge

   Processing customer feedback is a crucial aspect of the listening
   operation, and requires a flexible strategy. Whether that be through
   customer service or designated team members (stores, sales, etc.), you
   can process word-for-word feedback in order to react quickly and in a
   personnalized manner. Critizr for Business simplifies the process by
   acting as a central hub for your customers' feedback.

   Regardless of the interaction channel, all feedback is centralized
   within a single interface.
   TRAITEMENT V7

Measure customer satisfaction in real time

   Critizr provides you with real-time measurements of customer
   satisfaction down to the very last detail. By customizing questioning
   paths, you can create an efficient barometer based on indicators such
   as NPS or CSAT. Share information with your whole organization to
   involve everyone in a highly efficient, customer-centric approach.
   MESURE V6

Enhance the value of feedback to generate traffic

   Are we really able to target specific customers without knowing how
   satisfied they are ? We now know just how important customer
   satisfaction is. And yet, still, it remains an under-utilized element
   for marketing purposes. With Critizr for Business, cement customer
   feedbacks at the core of your strategy and thus improve the results of
   your marketing campaigns.
   VALORISATION V6
